1005
00:55:29,452 --> 00:55:31,662
"He asks to be raised up,

1006
00:55:31,829 --> 00:55:34,290
"and they put him
in a half-sitting posture.

1007
00:55:34,457 --> 00:55:36,834
"He called for mark
repeatedly,

1008
00:55:37,001 --> 00:55:39,086
"half deliriously,
all day.

1009
00:55:39,253 --> 00:55:43,090
"Life ebbs, runs now
with the speed of a millrace.

1010
00:55:43,257 --> 00:55:45,176
"His eyes turned back.

1011
00:55:45,343 --> 00:55:47,720
"A crowd, including
two or three doctors,

1012
00:55:47,887 --> 00:55:50,681
"several students,
and many soldiers,

1013
00:55:50,848 --> 00:55:52,767
"has silently gathered.

1014
00:55:52,933 --> 00:55:55,394
"The struggle goes on
and dwindles

1015
00:55:55,561 --> 00:55:58,105
"a little more
and a little more,

1016
00:55:58,272 --> 00:56:00,232
"and then welcome
oblivion,

1017
00:56:00,399 --> 00:56:02,693
"painlessness, death.

1018
00:56:02,860 --> 00:56:04,570
"A pause.

1019
00:56:04,737 --> 00:56:06,655
The crowd drops away."

1020
00:56:10,868 --> 00:56:13,579
"June 17, 1864.

1021
00:56:13,746 --> 00:56:15,039
"Dearest mother,

1022
00:56:15,206 --> 00:56:18,125
"this place seems to have got
the better of me.

1023
00:56:18,292 --> 00:56:21,212
I think I shall come home
for a short time."

1024
00:57:11,345 --> 00:57:12,471
"I think I understand

1025
00:57:12,638 --> 00:57:14,640
"the purpose
of the south properly

1026
00:57:14,807 --> 00:57:16,367
"and that the best way
to deal with them

1027
00:57:16,517 --> 00:57:19,562
"is to meet them fair
and square on any issue.

1028
00:57:19,728 --> 00:57:22,231
"We must fight them,
cut into them,

1029
00:57:22,398 --> 00:57:26,902
"NOT TALK TO THEM, AND PURSUE
TILL THEY CRY <i>ENOUGH.</i>

1030
00:57:27,069 --> 00:57:31,365
"War is the remedy
our enemies have chosen,

1031
00:57:31,532 --> 00:57:35,536
and I say let us give them
