1032
00:57:35,703 --> 00:57:37,580
William tecumseh sherman.

1033
00:57:39,874 --> 00:57:42,918
On the same day that Grant
stepped off into the wilderness,

1034
00:57:43,085 --> 00:57:44,795
sherman's grand army
of the west

1035
00:57:44,962 --> 00:57:47,214
moved south from chattanooga
towards Atlanta,

1036
00:57:47,381 --> 00:57:49,341
100 miles away.

1037
00:57:51,635 --> 00:57:54,263
William tecumseh sherman
and ulysses s. Grant

1038
00:57:54,430 --> 00:57:57,016
had survived
hard times together.

1039
00:57:57,183 --> 00:57:59,226
Their friendship
had been forged in Kentucky

1040
00:57:59,393 --> 00:58:01,562
when sherman had come close
to breaking down,

1041
00:58:01,729 --> 00:58:04,607
persuaded the war
would never end.

1042
00:58:04,773 --> 00:58:07,359
"Grant stood by me
when I was crazy,

1043
00:58:07,526 --> 00:58:09,528
"and I stood by him
when he was drunk,

1044
00:58:09,695 --> 00:58:13,657
and now we stand
by each other always."

1045
00:58:13,824 --> 00:58:15,576
Sherman was an orphan

1046
00:58:15,743 --> 00:58:18,287
and had graduated sixth
in his class at west point

1047
00:58:18,454 --> 00:58:20,539
when he was only 20.

1048
00:58:20,706 --> 00:58:23,918
Tall and red-haired,
intelligent and irritable,

1049
00:58:24,084 --> 00:58:26,212
he wore shoes
rather than military boots,

1050
00:58:26,378 --> 00:58:28,047
slept little,
and talked a lot.

1051
00:58:28,214 --> 00:58:31,258
"Boiling over with ideas,"
a friend said.

1052
00:58:31,425 --> 00:58:33,928
"He was always too busy
to eat much.

1053
00:58:34,094 --> 00:58:36,430
"He talked and smoked cigars
incessantly,

1054
00:58:36,597 --> 00:58:38,849
"giving orders,
dictating telegrams,

1055
00:58:39,016 --> 00:58:41,018
bright and chipper."

1056
00:58:41,185 --> 00:58:45,272
He hated politicians,
profiteers, sentimentalists.

1057
00:58:45,439 --> 00:58:47,358
Above all,
he hated reporters,

1058
00:58:47,525 --> 00:58:49,360
whom he considered
worse than spies

1059
00:58:49,527 --> 00:58:51,612
because they printed
military secrets

1060
00:58:51,779 --> 00:58:53,948
just to sell newspapers.

1061
00:58:54,114 --> 00:58:55,783
"These dirty
newspaper scribblers

1062
00:58:55,950 --> 00:58:57,368
"have the impudence
of Satan.

1063
00:58:57,535 --> 00:59:00,579
"They come into camp, poke about
among the lazy shirks,

1064
00:59:00,746 --> 00:59:04,375
"and pick up their camp rumors
and publish them as facts.

1065
00:59:04,542 --> 00:59:05,960
"They are a pest,

1066
00:59:06,126 --> 00:59:10,464
and I treat them as spies,
which, in truth, they are."

1067
00:59:10,631 --> 00:59:12,552
He was convinced
if he killed them all,

1068
00:59:12,716 --> 00:59:16,804
there would be news from hell
before breakfast.

1069
00:59:16,971 --> 00:59:20,140
Family and friends
called him "cump."

1070
00:59:20,307 --> 00:59:22,685
His men called him
"uncle Billy."

1071
00:59:22,851 --> 00:59:26,105
He was ruthless in war.

1072
00:59:28,274 --> 00:59:29,775
Now Grant entrusted
his friend

1073
00:59:29,942 --> 00:59:31,360
with the second
most important part

1074
00:59:31,527 --> 00:59:33,279
of his grand strategy--

1075
00:59:33,445 --> 00:59:36,782
to seize Atlanta and smash
the combined confederate armies

1076
00:59:36,949 --> 00:59:40,703
of Tennessee and Mississippi
under Joseph e. Johnston.

1077
00:59:49,503 --> 00:59:50,796
In Washington,

1078
00:59:50,963 --> 00:59:53,924
Lincoln's chances
for reelection were slim.

1079
00:59:54,091 --> 00:59:57,011
"I'm going to be beaten,"
Lincoln wrote that summer,

1080
00:59:57,177 --> 00:59:59,680
"and unless some
great change takes place,

1081
00:59:59,847 --> 01:00:01,515
badly beaten."

1082
01:00:01,682 --> 01:00:03,642
With Grant stalled
at Petersburg,

1083
01:00:03,809 --> 01:00:06,562
sherman had to win.

1084
01:00:13,694 --> 01:00:15,613
Sherman had surveyed
parts of Georgia

1085
01:00:15,779 --> 01:00:17,323
as a young lieutenant.

1086
01:00:17,489 --> 01:00:20,618
"I knew Georgia better than
the rebels did," he wrote.

1087
01:00:20,784 --> 01:00:23,370
He knew the fighting there
would be scattered and sporadic,

1088
01:00:23,537 --> 01:00:25,831
"a big Indian war,"
he called it.

1089
01:00:30,961 --> 01:00:32,296
Joseph e. Johnston,

1090
01:00:32,463 --> 01:00:34,590
the confederate commander
who now faced sherman,

1091
01:00:34,757 --> 01:00:38,218
was heartily disliked
by president Jefferson Davis,

1092
01:00:38,385 --> 01:00:42,723
but he was very nearly
worshiped by his men.

1093
01:00:42,890 --> 01:00:45,392
"I do not believe
there was a soldier in his army

1094
01:00:45,559 --> 01:00:47,811
"but would gladly
have died for him.

1095
01:00:47,978 --> 01:00:50,773
"With him,
everything was his soldiers.

1096
01:00:50,939 --> 01:00:54,068
He would feed his soldiers
if the country starved."

